{#- §09 THE FINANCE STACK (CFO value rests on accurate books — prose) — white (LAST bespoke) -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="fractional-cfo-stack">
  <div class="ct read">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">The finance stack</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:24ch;margin-bottom:24px;">CFO work only delivers value on accurate books.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>The first thing a fractional CFO does on a new engagement is assess the operational accounting underneath. If the books are unreliable &mdash; uncategorized transactions, unreconciled accounts, missing payroll integration, a sloppy chart of accounts &mdash; the CFO must either fix the books first (slow and expensive at CFO rates) or produce analysis on a foundation that can&rsquo;t be trusted (worse).</p>
      <p>TechBrot offers fractional CFO precisely because we already operate the bookkeeping layer cleanly. Engagements that pair fractional CFO with TechBrot <a href="/accounting/bookkeeping/monthly-bookkeeping/?intent=monthly">bookkeeping</a>, <a href="/accounting/payroll-management/?intent=payroll">payroll</a>, and <a href="/accounting/sales-tax-compliance/?intent=sales-tax">sales tax</a> underneath deliver more value &mdash; the CFO works from accurate books from day one, integration costs disappear, and the finance stack runs as one system instead of three vendors. The pairing isn&rsquo;t required, but when CFO and bookkeeping run together, the math gets simpler.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
